Connect4Base - Class in game.games.connect4
Class which is used for basic Connect4 Logic, namely transforming a current gamestate to an array of doubles, visualizing a gamestate, making a neural net choose a move with a given gamestate, checking if the game is finished and updating the board after a turn Note that a gamestate is defined as a sequence of doubles (double array), since this represents the inputs of Neural Nets and Genomes
